tr.td: The file size was not "m"'ed. the official logo has the viewbox. If really needed I'll make a proper logo without viewbox under another name.

tr.td: Latest official version from W3C: http://www.w3.org/html/logo/downloads/HTML5_Logo.svg . No xml version, svg version, encoding, doctype declarations needed, also passed W3C's validation test. Considered as a doctype of "SVG 1.1+IRI, XHTML5+ARIA plus MathM

tr.td: Added viewBox to the mark-up, this way embedding the SVG directly in HTML pages is possible (via the object tag for instance). Also added the title element ("HTML5").

tr.td: sorry the previous one lacked the xmlns

tr.td: minified. btw, I uploaded the original version here: File:HTML5 Logo.svg. The original version is actually colored, but there's something not supported by MediaWiki
